HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 798
By Hemmer
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Dave Owens, 2025
NWTF Grand National Calling Champion.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly recognize those
individuals whose extraordinary accomplishments bring distinction to their field and reflect
positively on events hosted in the great State of Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, one such individual is Dave Owens, who was named Senior Division
Champion at the 2025 Grand National Calling Championships, held during the annual
convention of the National Wild Turkey Federation (NWTF) in Nashville; a contest widely
regarded as the "Super Bowl" of the turkey calling world, the event represents the pinnacle of
competitive turkey calling and draws the finest callers from across the nation; and
WHEREAS, in the final moments of the 2025 competition, Dave Owens stood alongside
nine-time champion Matt Van Cise as one of the last two contenders, ultimately being named
the winner of this highly coveted event; and
WHEREAS, this championship marks the fulfillment of a longtime goal for Mr. Owens,
whose win was not only a personal triumph but a moment of recognition for a philosophy of
hunting rooted in authenticity, perseverance, and respect for wild turkeys; and
WHEREAS, Dave Owens, who resides in Cherokee, Alabama, has deep experience in
turkey hunting and competitive calling, having previously won the 2018 Grand National Senior
Division Open Champion title and the Georgia State Championship; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Owens is the founder of the Pinhoti Project, a video series that presents
turkey hunting in a realistic and minimalist style, showcasing a more accessible, effort-based
approach that places the focus on the wild turkey itself and the experience of the hunt; and
HJR0798
011675
- 1 -

WHEREAS, in addition to his work as a hunter, videographer, and championship caller,
Dave Owens serves on the board of Turkeys for Tomorrow, a nonprofit conservation
organization committed to science-based management practices that benefit wild turkey
populations and other wildlife species; and
WHEREAS, Dave Owens is known for his commitment to helping others, as
demonstrated by his involvement with the KT Team, an organization that assists disabled
hunters in enjoying the outdoors and overcoming challenges in the field; and
WHEREAS, through his championship title, his conservation leadership, and his widely
respected media work, Mr. Owens has become a key figure in the hunting community and
continues to inspire others with his dedication to ethical hunting and wildlife stewardship; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Dave Owens upon his victory at the 2025
NWTF Grand National Calling Championship, recognize his ongoing contributions to the future
of turkey hunting and conservation, and extend to him our best wishes for continued success in
his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
